An activity has
  an action string,
  a date date/time,
  a control string,
  a course string.

To register an activity:
  put "D:\cal-4700 initiative\CMS\seguimiento.txt"  into a path.
  if the path is not in the file system, create the path in the file system.
  read the path into a buffer called original.
  put the activity's action then " - "  then the activity's control then " - "  then the activity's course into a string called auxiliar.
  append " - " then the activity's date's string to the auxiliar.  
  write the original then the auxiliar then the crlf string to the path. 
  If the i/o error is not blank, write the i/o error on the console.

